# Any of a group of [[organic]] [[compound]]s including the [[fat]]s, [[oil]]s, [[wax]]es, [[sterol]]s, [[nucleic acid]]s, and [[triglyceride]]s. Lipids are characterized by being [[insoluble]] in water, and account for most of the fat present in the human body.  They are, however, soluble in [[nonpolar]] organic [[solvent]]s.

